<p>This is a collaboration SCP between me (Amuness Creeps), Dr Hysteria, and Voct.<br />
RIP The SCiP Console</p>
<p><tt><em>Don't worry Philip&#8230; Daddy's coming to save you&#8230;</em></tt><br />
<tt><em>I have all the time in the world&#8230;</em></tt></p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Project Time:</strong> 52 days</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Image credits:</strong> Credit goes to Faminepulse for the first image of the article. The image of the road belong to me.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Credits for critique:</strong> A shit ton of people: Roget, MrAnakinSpecter, MrWrong, A Random Day, DreamwalkerFae, WrongJohnSilver, Waxx, Bennings, AJMansfield and TyGently. if I forgot anyone, then tell me.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Special Thanks:</strong> Special thanks goes to Dr Hysteria for finding the image. A very special thanks goes to Voct for doing a major amount of edits towards the article to make it amazing. Voct thanks a TON. Really.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>Post:</strong> This is an SCP that I thought up while walking one day. It just came the fuck outta nowhere and I <strong>had</strong> to use it. I always wanted to do an SCP where you try and get something you love back&#8230;but you don't end up getting cause <em>shit happens man.</em> Originally, this SCP was suppose to be neutralized with Alexander never getting his son back. The loop ends, but thinks he got his son back from some phenomenon. Also, there's an easter egg within the SCP. No cheating.</p>
<p>EDIT: Aww fuck yeah! 40 upvotes! &gt;8D</p>
<p>EDIT2: I swear if this get to 50+, hooooollllllyyyy shit!</p>
<p>EDIT3: This page got a translation into Russian! <a href="http://scpfoundation.ru/scp-694">http://scpfoundation.ru/scp-694</a></p>
<p>EDIT4: 50 upvotes?! GOT 'EM!</p>
<p>EDIT5: And it got a Chinese translation! <a href="http://scpfoundation.123ubb.com/t6079-topic">http://scpfoundation.123ubb.com/t6079-topic</a></p>

